{"履修期": "秋学期後半", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "Global Supply Chain Management:This\ncourse addresses what I call a \"boundary issue\" of multinational\nbusiness management, focusing on the interfaces among product/service\ndevelopment, procurement, and marketing activities on a global basis. Since the\n1990s, increased outsourcing of manufacturing activities and services has\nbecome a prominent part of the restructuring of firms’ supply chains. Academics\nand consultancy firms have largely supported the view of outsourcing as one of\nthe key drivers of superior performance. As we are now increasingly\ndiscovering, the drawbacks of outsourcing, or put differently, the advantages\nof vertical integration, have been underestimated or even neglected. In this\ncourse, we explore a more balanced view of global supply chain management (sourcing\nstrategy) and the performance of the firm. For managers we provide indications\nof how they can achieve the required balance.&nbsp;", "到達目標": "The fundamental premise underlying global supply chain\nmanagement is the boundary-spanning nature of the topic, encompassing all\naspects of product development to product delivery mechanisms, involving\nR&amp;D, manufacturing, and marketing on a global basis. Global supply chain\nmanagement must be market-driven, and calls for not just cost reduction in the\nmovement of materials, components, and products but also achieving customer\nsatisfaction. The key challenges for business organizations include developing\na shared vision throughout the organization about 1) how cost-efficiently the\nmarket should be served and 2) how effectively customer satisfaction should be accomplished.\nPursuing the minimization of total cost in global supply chain does not\nnecessarily correspond to the maximization of customer satisfaction. Indeed,\nachieving customer satisfaction can be costly. At the end of the course, you\nwill learn to acquire a strategic thought process to accomplish this balancing\nact in delivering the product to the customer. You will also learn the changing\nnature of global competition and the importance of the simultaneous pursuit of\neconomies of scale and cultural sensitivities in global supply chain management.&nbsp;", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "International Business, International Marketing", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "Face to face class format.The course is\ntaught, using a combination of lectures, case analysis, and class discussion.\nThe textbook will give you a broad picture of what global supply chain\nmanagement is and how it affects corporate performance.&nbsp;\n\nTo enhance your\ngrasp and management of various problems associated with global supply chain,\nyou are required to work in a group on both Assignments (A) Case Analysis and (B) Case-Writing Group Project. Each group\nwill be made up of a number of students and will work as a unit for all group\nassignments throughout the semester. A comprehensive exam is also scheduled as\nAssignment (C) to assess your understanding of the class material.", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:3.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:3.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;\"><strong><span times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:;\">Global Supply Chain Management as an Academic Subject (1)</span></strong></p>", "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:3.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:3.0pt;margin-left:16.95pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:12.0pt;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-family:Wingdings;font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:wingdings;mso-bidi-font-family:wingdings;\">§<span times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\";\"=\"roman';'\" style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-size-adjust:none;font-kerning:auto;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-sett